The article discusses the defense and security cooperation between the United States and the Baltic countries of Estonia, Latvia, and Lithuania. As NATO allies, these countries are committed to mutual defense and building national resilience. The United States provides security assistance to improve defense infrastructure and strengthen national resilience. The countries also participate in multinational training events with U.S. forces. They have been valued participants in NATO's missions in Afghanistan and are active members of the Global Coalition to Counter ISIL. In terms of economic cooperation, the article highlights efforts to increase bilateral trade and support the U.S.-EU Transatlantic Trade and Investment Partnership. Educational and professional exchange programs are also mentioned, as well as the preservation of cultural heritage through cultural festivals and events.